chunk_content: DOMAIN - HEALTHY 1.1 KEY OBJECTIVE - INCREASE DIAGNOSIS OF HIV INFECTION 1.1.1. BENCHMARK: All children, adolescents, and caregivers in the household have known HIV status or a test is not required based on risk assessment DATA SOURCES AND DEFINITIONS: ● Caregivers self-reported HIV-positive or negative test results for children (0-9 years)/adolescents (10-17 years) ● For children without HIV status reported by caregivers, case manager has completed a PEPFAR approved HIV risk assessment for children/adolescent showing HIV test not indicated ● Caregivers self-reported HIV test results for HIV-Exposed Infants (HEI) at 18 months of age or at least 1 week after cessation of breastfeeding, whichever comes later ● Caregivers self-reported HIV-positive or negative test results ● For caregivers without HIV status reported, the case manager has completed the PEPFAR HIV risk assessment showing HIV test not indicated 1.2.
